st trueshot at about skill 155, got it on the second try, i tried at skill 100, 112, 120, 130 and then i decided to wait.<P>Alone Starwalker - 42th Ranger on CT</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">vizco</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've failed fourteen times at skill levels from 108 up to current 131. Sigh. Tips I've gotten include:<P>1) Buf up your WIS (will raise skill faster). INT allegedly increases success probability, WIS skill increase probability. You can buy cheap +WIS items for a ten or more point level increase (+3 jasper earrings and rings, savant's cap, etc.), total expenditure under 100pp. Skill level, according to reasonable tests, has much much more effect than stats, so buf WIS to increase skill level faster.<P>2) Keep your bowyering book open while making it (and your fletching book open while fletching). No confirmation of this rumor, but "people say" it increases success prob a bit. No cost, so why not do it?<P>3) I suggest collecting as many copies of the "materials" as you can carry (buy extra backpacks). One long camp for micro servos is easier than several short ones (for me at least). Also, the more Kiola nuts you can cram into containers the less often you have to take that boat ride.  (There is enough time to buy 30 of them during the brief boat stop).<P>   - Vizco<BR>     Ranger 34, Prexus</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">tfactor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hail,<P>I have yet to try to make mine, sad at 15th level aye.  I have not had the time to sit and raise my fletching very much only in the thirties.  And frankly I have lost all hope in archery being good for combat.<P>I still intend to make it one day as I have a bunch of servos and webs in the bank.  Where do I get the nuts at?  What else will I need.  Thanks</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Epicurus Quickli</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The nuts are at Eurids crossing between the big Q and Odus.<P>------------------<BR>Epi/Brood<BR>GoH of Test<BR>Healin and Barshin Norath daily<p>[This message has been edited by Epicurus Quickli (edited 08-25-2000).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Oakao</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nuts are In Ocean of Tears first stop after leaving east freeport. Run to hut/Inn buy a bunch, run back to boat, you might catch it if you are quick.<BR>Treant Wood is gotten from Jyle Windshot in W Freeport (there is an imposter in E Freeport). Jyle is in the Hog callers Inn (upstairs) and wants a small lantern for the wood.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">equin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">have heard that 160 is a good skill rating for success... like 4 out of 6<P>also recommend bumping up wis and int. got my wis to 111 and int to 94 for a woodelf.<P>sold books... hmmm, maybe i need to go back and buy<P>was told that the top bow with cams and darkwood takes like 180 to be successful... sames stats as trueshot but faster.<P>- Equin</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">maco</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I was lucky and got one first try at 81.  I have been making bows all along though and maybe that made the difference.  I have made about 50 or 60 bows, and my success rate for <BR>a Trival bow is like 9 out of 10, has been since trivial.  I do have to admit, my skill is still at 82 as once you make the Trueshot, you have a great bow and the arrows are very expensive to make at this level.  Good luck to all.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Callixii</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I made my 